    heroImage="https://images.pexels.com/photos/2846217/pexels-photo-2846217.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=1600&h=600&fit=crop"
    overviewEn="Brazil and China share one of the world's most dynamic bilateral trade relationships. China is Brazil's largest trading partner, with over USD 150 billion in annual trade. This has created a significant corridor for international money transfers — from Brazilian importers paying Chinese suppliers, to Chinese workers in Brazil sending money home, to Brazilian businesses investing in China. The BRL-CNY corridor has grown substantially in recent years, driven by both trade flows and a growing Chinese community in Brazil, estimated at over 200,000 people."
    overviewZh="巴西和中国共享世界上最具活力的双边贸易关系之一。中国是巴西最大的贸易伙伴，年贸易额超过1500亿美元。这为国际汇款创造了重要走廊——从巴西进口商向中国供应商付款，到在巴西工作的中国工人向国内汇款，再到巴西企业在中国投资。雷亚尔-人民币走廊近年来大幅增长，由贸易流动和巴西不断增长的中国社区（估计超过20万人）共同推动。"
    tip1En="Check CNY receiving restrictions: China has capital controls that limit how much foreign currency can be received in some accounts. Verify with the recipient before sending large amounts."
    tip1Zh="检查人民币接收限制：中国有资本管制，限制某些账户可接收的外币金额。在汇送大额款项前请与收款人核实。"
    tip2En="Use specialized BRL-CNY platforms: Services like PandaRemit specialize in the Brazil-China corridor and typically offer better rates than generic international transfer services."
    tip2Zh="使用专业的雷亚尔-人民币平台：PandaRemit等服务专注于巴西-中国走廊，通常比通用国际转账服务提供更好的汇率。"
    tip3En="Account for Chinese New Year: Transfer volumes spike around Chinese New Year (late January/February), which can sometimes affect processing times. Plan transfers in advance."
    tip3Zh="考虑中国春节因素：中国春节（1月底至2月）前后汇款量激增，有时可能影响处理时间。请提前规划汇款。"
    communityEn="Brazil is home to one of the largest Chinese communities in Latin America, concentrated in São Paulo's Liberdade district — historically a Japanese neighborhood that has evolved into a broader Asian cultural center. The Chinese-Brazilian community includes long-established families, recent migrants, and business professionals who maintain close ties with mainland China, Hong Kong, and Taiwan."
    communityZh="巴西拥有拉丁美洲最大的华人社区之一，集中在圣保罗的解放区——历史上的日本人聚居区，已演变为更广泛的亚洲文化中心。在巴西的华人社区包括已在此定居的家庭、近年移民和商业专业人士，他们与中国大陆、香港和台湾保持密切联系。"
    regulatoryEn="Brazil permits transfers to China subject to Banco Central do Brasil reporting requirements. For business transfers, a commercial invoice or contract is required. China's receiving rules require that personal transfers comply with annual foreign exchange quotas (USD 50,000 per individual per year under Chinese regulations). For business payments, documentation of the underlying transaction is needed."
    regulatoryZh="巴西允许向中国转账，须符合巴西中央银行的报告要求。商业转账需要提供商业发票或合同。中国的接收规则要求个人转账符合年度外汇配额（中国法规规定每人每年5万美元）。商业付款需要提供基础交易的文件证明。"
